==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imperator
<hw>Im`pe*ra"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Emperor</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A commander; a
leader; an emperor; -- originally an appellation of honor by which Roman
soldiers saluted their general after an important victory. Subsequently
the title was conferred as a recognition of great military achievements
by the senate, whence it carried with it some special privileges. After
the downfall of the Republic it was assumed by Augustus and his
successors, and came to have the meaning now attached to the word
<altname>emperor</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imperatorial</ent>⟦br⟧
